Sri Lanka 33 for one in follow-on, trail Australia by 234 runs 
Sri Lanka were 33 for one in their second innings after being forced to
follow on against Australia at the close on the third day of the second
cricket test at the Melbourne Cricket Ground here Thursday.
The Sri Lankans were dismissed for 233 in their first innings to trail
Australia's 500 for six declared by 267 runs.
At stumps with two days to play, Chandika Hathurusinghe was not out 20
with Asanka Gurusinha on eight.
